Fiat says not interested in Russian AvtoVAZ . Italy ' s Fiat group has no interest whatsoever in taking over Russia ' s indebted carmaker AvtoVAZ , Fiat Managing Director Paolo Cantarella said . A senior Russian minister on Tuesday called for bankruptcy authorities to start proceedings against AvtoVAZ , which the government says is one of the country ' s biggest tax debtors . Talking to reporters while attending a meeting of Fiat managers in Turin , Cantarella said : " We have already said that we are not interested . " AvtoVAZ ' s main Lada car is based on a 1960s or 1970s Fiat model and Russian sources had speculated that the Turin - based giant might be interested in taking over the ailing company . - - Milan newsroom + 392 66129589 
